cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper deals with the problem of robots understanding spatial relations and placing objects accordingly. This involves computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) techniques, as well as artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (LG) methods for training a neural network. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques for understanding relational instructions. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.RO, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.CL.
